<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-08-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="160" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d160">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-08-12"><hi rend="italic">August 12, 1903</hi></date>.
                                (Received 15.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>August 12, 7 p.m. The treaty was rejected by the Senate to-day in its
                            entirety. Confidential. Do not accept this as final. There is still some
                            hope. Wait for further advices.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>